HEADWORD: Dehydration
<hw>De`hy*dra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>The act or process of freeing from water; also, the condition of a
body from which the water has been removed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dehydrogenate</ent>⟦br⟧
